<ul>
    <li><strong>The Dangerous Lie:</strong> "If I just work harder, stay later, be more available, things will get better." (They won't.)</li>
    <li><strong>The Unsustainable Model:</strong> Trying to do it all yourself makes you the bottleneck—and guarantees burnout.</li>
    <li><strong>The Paradigm Shift:</strong> Real impact doesn't come from doing more; it comes from building systems that work without you.</li>
</ul>
